cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.MM, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the technical details of LTE operation in the unlicensed spectrum and its coexistence capabilities with legacy systems, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper may involve information theory concepts related to wireless communication and signal processing.
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper discusses the proposed variants of LTE operation in the unlicensed spectrum, which is related to communications and networking.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may involve multimedia applications and services that can benefit from LTE operation in the unlicensed spectrum.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may involve system-level analysis and control of LTE operation in the unlicensed spectrum.
